results.content: The domain namesexample.com, example.net, example.org, and example.edu are second-level domain names in the Domain Name System of the Internet. results.content: When a client connects tohttps://www.example.com, it will start with the SSL negotiation, and the user will get a warning that the SSL certificate does not match. Any redirect that you create will happen only after the SSL negotiation, so they will still be getting the SSL certificate warning.

results.title: If example.com is a legit website, does that mean 123.example.com is ...
results.content: It's extremely important to know that dots can only exist in domain names as a way to separate different levels, and no other character can be used as a separator. So 123-example.com is not owned by whoever ownsexample.com; it's a completely different domain.
